# Code style

## TypeScript
- Strict. No `any` without a short justification.
- Prefer `type` for props and DTOs. Reuse `client/src/shared/lib/types.ts` in the client.

## Imports
- Client: `@/` → `client/src/*` (Vite alias).
- Server: `@/` → `server/src/*` (Next alias).

## React (client)
- Functional components. Hooks where needed.
- Prefer feature-local state; lift only when shared across routes.

## Errors & logging
- User-facing: clear `Error` messages. Log with `console.error("context", err)` where useful.

## Money
- Use `formatILS()` from venue-pricing. Do not scatter `₪` formatting.

## Server (when added)
- Validate and clamp numbers server-side if the server ever persists user data.
